                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-07-14T12:45:00-04:00"
                            notBefore="1919-07-11T16:00:00+04:53">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received July 14, 1919, 12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following from [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at] Omsk.</p>
                <p>[“]319, July 11, 4 p.m. Situation at front. Since July 8th Ekaterinburg being
                    officially evacuated. Plan of Russian Army is to withdraw behind Tiumen. Have
                    advised American Red Cross to evacuate Cheliabinsk and Tiumen. Russian Red Cross
                    evacuating all patients from Ekaterinburg to Omsk, <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName> has returned from front. Have not yet interviewed him.
                        <persName corresp="#p_GGGR1">Gaida</persName>’s services with Siberian Army
                    terminated on 8th. Bolsheviki apparently using Hindenburg tactics of
                    concentrating all available forces on <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName>’s front with object of taking Ekaterinburg and
                    Cheliabinsk thus occupying whole of Urals and farming and industrial districts.
                    Thereafter Bolsheviki may throw bulk of forces against Denekine or continue to
                    Omsk. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RPS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
